in the completed class of M on F p n for p = 3, 5, 7, 11 and n = 4, when c ∈ F ∗ p n is not a squire. Actually in these ﬁelds the proposition above can be stated as \u201dif and only if\u201d claim.\nTheorem 5: The bent function f (x) = Tr n (cx d ) over F 3 n , where n = 2k ≥ 6, d = t(3 k − 1) with gcd(t, 3 k + 1) = 1, and c ∈ F 3 n with K(c 3 k +1 ) = 0, does not belong to the completed class of M when t = 3 i + w for some nonnegative i and 0 ≤ w ≤ 2.\nProof: We just sketch the proof here since it is similar to the ones of Theorems 1-3. We can assume without loss of generality that 0 ≤ i ≤ k − 1.\nLet ﬁrst w = 0. Then we can assume that i = 0. We have d = 3 k − 1 = 2(3 k−1 + 3 k−2 + ... + 1) = 0 ... 0\nIn (x + a) d all the monomials are of the type x t with t = ( 0 ... 0 t k−1 ... t 0 ) where t 0 , ..., t k−1 ∈ {0, 1, 2}. Let t = 0 ... 0\nmod (p n − 1), 1 ≤ i ≤ n − 1 and that any cyclic shift of any vector t, t = t , of the form above is different from t . Hence x t has the coefﬁcient 4a 4 in (x + a) d , and therefore it has coefﬁcient 4c((a + b) 4 − a 4 − b 4 ) = 4c(ab 3 + a 3 b) in D a,b f . If D a,a f ≡ 0 for some a ∈ F ∗ 3 n then a 4 = 0, a contradiction.\nmonomial x t has the coefﬁcient c((a+b) 3 k+i +3 i −a 3 k+i +3 i − b 3 k+i +3 i ) = c(a 3 k+i b 3 i + a 3 i b 3 k+i ) in D a,b f . If D a,a f ≡ 0 for some a ∈ F ∗ 3 n then a 3 k+i +3 i = 0, a contradiction.\nsee that the monomial x t has the coefﬁcient c((a + b) 3 i +1 − a 3 i +1 − b 3 i +1 ) = c(ab 3 i + a 3 i b) in D a,b f . If D a,a f ≡ 0 for some a ∈ F ∗ 3 n then a 3 i +1 = 0, a contradiction."},"refs":[{"authors":[{"name":"P. V. Kumar"},{"name":"R. A. Scholtz"},{"name":"L. R. Welch"}],"title":{"text":"Generalized bent functions and their properties"}},{"authors":[{"name":"X.-D. Hou"}],"title":{"text":"p-Ary and q-ary versions of certain results about bent functions and resilient functions"}},{"authors":[{"name":"Y. Tan"},{"name":"A. Pott"},{"name":"T. Feng"}],"title":{"text":"Strongly regular graphs ass